  "datePublished": "2016-04-28",
  "description": "In your original letter, you stated:\nI keep hearing that Bernie can still win, and that he\u0026rsquo;s the only one who can beat Trump in a general election. What\u0026rsquo;s your take on that?\nBernie\u0026rsquo;s \u0026ldquo;lead\u0026rdquo; in the general comes only from the #BernieorBust movement, which based on demographics aren\u0026rsquo;t incredibly likely to vote in the general anyway.\nYour argument for why your candidate is more likely to win is because your candidate has supporters who would throw the election to Trump if he doesn\u0026rsquo;t get the nomination.\n",
  "name": "Bernie Sanders still can't win",
